In this statement, President Obama addresses the investigation into IRS personnel who improperly screened conservative groups applying for tax-exempt status. He expresses his anger and states that the misconduct uncovered is inexcusable. The President emphasizes the need for the IRS to operate with integrity and for the government to conduct itself in a way that is true to the public trust. He outlines the actions that will be taken in response to this issue, including holding responsible parties accountable, implementing new safeguards to prevent similar behavior in the future, and working with Congress to address the problem. The President concludes by emphasizing the importance of enforcing the law in a fair and impartial way and ensuring clarity in the laws to avoid ambiguity.